                    <div class="card-text">
                        <section>
                            <span class="textFont">In 2002 our founding family established Mumbai's first and only shelter and hospital for ownerless animals.
                                As word spread, a few rescue requests a week became more than 100 calls each day. Tens of thousands of
                                animals have been rescued and saved, and the community's compassion has blossomed into action.</span>
                        </section>
                        <section>
                            <span class="textFont">In 1994 PawDopt’s founders Erika, Jim and daughter Claire began travelling from their home in Seattle, USA,
                                 to India, where they fell in love with the country, and especially the city of Mumbai.</span>
                        </section>
                        <section>
                            <span class="textFont">When they realised there were no services for ownerless animals in Mumbai, they contacted animal
                                organizations around the world, and began to learn what they could do to help. This is when their life work
                                of learning how to rescue animals, hiring and training staff, and raising funds for medicine and food began.
                                In 2002 they hired a veterinarian and began training local villagers in animal care, rented a small piece of
                                land and slowly started to rescue injured animals.</span>
                        </section>
                    </div>
